Class IncludeLogEntry

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.facebook.buck.cxx.IncludeLogEntry

  • @ParametersAreNonnullByDefault
 @Generated(value={"Immutables.generator","AbstractIncludeLogEntry"})

public final class IncludeLogEntry
extends Object
    Represents an entry in an IncludeLog instance, i.e. each "inclusion event" during the generation of a source file's preprocessed output.

    • Method Detail

      • id

        public int id()
        Indicates order of inclusions happening. Just an increasing number assigned to each. Is unique so that lower id means it happened before another IncludeLogEntry.

      • getParent

        public Optional<IncludeLogEntry> getParent()
        The inclusion event that led to the inclusion of _this_ one's includer. E.g. if "foo.h" includes "bar.h", the parent is the inclusion event for, e.g. when "foo.cpp" included "foo.h". If included by the main file, this is not present.

      • getOrigCurrentFile

        public Path getOrigCurrentFile()
        Which file did the inclusion. See MorePaths#fixPath(Path) for how the path given to the constructor is cleaned up prior to memoizing it here.

      • getCurrentFile

        public Path getCurrentFile()
        Returns:
        The computed-at-construction value of the currentFile attribute

      • getInclusionKind

        public com.facebook.buck.cxx.AbstractIncludeLogEntry.InclusionKind getInclusionKind()
        String representing the kind of inclusion performed. Known examples:
        • #include
        • #include_next
        • #import if you're into Objective-C/C++
        • #__include_macros produced by Clang if you did -imacros on the command line.

        • getQuoteKind

          public com.facebook.buck.cxx.AbstractIncludeLogEntry.QuoteKind getQuoteKind()
          how this was included, i.e. #include &lt;foo&gt; or #include "bar.h".

        • getParameter

          public String getParameter()
          The path that was included, in a literal sense. Examples:
          • ./foo.c does #include "bar.h": result is bar.h
          • ./foo.c does #include "./bar.h": result is ./bar.h
          • somepath/foo.c does #include "bar.h": result is bar.h

          There's little logic in determining this string; it's just the text between quote marks / angle brackets.

        • getOrigNextFile

          public Path getOrigNextFile()
          The path that was included, after resolution w/r/t the includer. Only affects quoted includes.
          • ./foo.c does #include "bar.h": result is bar.h for gcc, ./bar.h for clang.
          • ./foo.c does #include "./bar.h": result is ./bar.h
          • somepath/foo.c does #include "bar.h", where "bar.h" is in the same dir as foo.c: result is somepath/bar.h
          See MorePaths#fixPath(Path) for how the path given to the constructor is cleaned up prior to memoizing it here.

        • getNextFile

          public Path getNextFile()
          The path that was included, after resolution w/r/t the includer. See getOrigNextFile(). See MorePaths#fixPath(Path) for how the path given to the constructor is cleaned up prior to memoizing it here.
